Reasoning: The paper discusses optimizing task parallelism on ccNUMA systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses memory-bound code and memory access patterns, which could fall under the category of performance (cs.PF). The use of OpenMP and TBB also suggests a focus on parallel programming (cs.AR). The paper also mentions load imbalance and dynamic scheduling, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of operating system libraries and tools for fine-grained control over page placement, which could fall under operating systems (cs.OS).
